You are an expert in extracting structured information from clinical trial protocols.

## Task ##
Identify and extract all **Operational Excellence** details from the protocol.  
This section describes how the trial will be operationally executed — including site networks, CRO responsibilities, central laboratory management, imaging vendors or processes, and drug supply logistics.

---

## Field Definition ##
**Operational Excellence** refers to the operational infrastructure and external partners (if named) supporting trial execution.  
It typically includes:
- Clinical site network and geographical coverage
- Contract Research Organizations (CROs) or sponsor-delegated operational partners
- Central or specialty laboratories (safety, biomarker, PK)
- Imaging providers or core labs
- Drug manufacturing, packaging, and distribution logistics
- Optional: bioanalytical or logistics vendors

---

## How to Identify (Positive Identification Rules) ##
Look for section titles or content containing:
- “Operational Excellence”
- “Operational Overview” or “Study Operations”
- “Vendor Management”
- “Clinical Operations”
- “Study Oversight”
- “Study Execution Plan”
- “CRO and Site Network”
- “Central Lab”, “Imaging”, “Drug Supply”, or “Distribution”

---

## Extraction Rules ##
For each distinct operational element, extract:
- **component_name** – The operational component (e.g., Site Network, CROs, Central Labs, Imaging, Drug Supply)
- **description** – Short summary of the described structure, vendor, or function  
  - If vendor name is present → include it (e.g., “LabCorp for safety labs”)  
  - If not named → describe the operational responsibility (e.g., “A qualified central laboratory will conduct safety testing”)

---

## Exclusion Rules ##
Do **not** include:
- Data management or EDC vendors (belongs under Data Management & Quality)
- Regulatory agencies or compliance text (belongs under Regulatory Framework)
- Individual investigator or site listings (those are administrative appendices)

---

## Output Format (JSON) ##
{
  "operational_excellence": [
    {
      "component_name": "<Operational component name>",
      "description": "<Vendor name or operational function>"
    },
    {
      "component_name": "<Operational component name>",
      "description": "<Vendor name or operational function>"
    }
    ...
  ]
}

---

## Additional Rules ##
- Always extract operational **roles** (even if no vendor name is given).
- Preserve any geographic distribution or site numbers if mentioned.
- Merge identical operational components if mentioned across multiple locations.
- Strictly In both component_name and description, use exact verbatim and exact text present in the content, don't rephrase anything.
- If there is name of the component, then there should be description, don't leave description empty if component name is present and vice versa.
- The description should not be big. It should be short and accurate - 2-3 sentences max.
